<div class="container">
    <h1 class="heading-primary" id="title">FAQuestions</h1>
    <div class="accordion" style="font-family:Sanchez, serif">
        <dl>
            <dt>
                <a href="#accordion1" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion1" class="accordion-title accordionTitle js-accordionTrigger" style="font-size:17px">What is considered mythical, mystical, or just fantastic creature?</a>
            </dt>
            <dd class="accordion-content accordionItem is-collapsed scrollable" id="accordion" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size:15px">
                <p>We truly believe that all animals are fantastic but as to which animals we will accept into our resorts is determined by several factors.</p>
                <p>1) The animal unfortunately cannot be one that is typically found in a zoo, park, or wildlife sanctuary.  Such animals would be considered "exotic" pets, not mythical.</p>
                <p>2) The animal would have to be involved in some form of legend, with special properties not found in typical animals ie. fire-breathing, shape-shifting, extra heads. Animals that have the appearance of our known world's beasts but have special properties (for example, nightmares which are fire-breathing black horses) would be accepted only after testing and much needed proof(such as published stories or historical texts).</p>
            </dd>
            <dt>
                <a href="#accordion2" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion2" class="accordion-title accordionTitle js-accordionTrigger" style="font-size:17px">
                    Will you accept any regular or exotic, domesticated animals at your resorts?
                </a>
            </dt>
            <dd class="accordion-content accordionItem is-collapsed scrollable" id="accordion2" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size:15px">
                <p>Unfortunately, no.  As much as we would love to take care of animals of all kinds, we do not want to take business away from those who do this kind of work regularly.  We thought it would be in the best interests of our customers and other pet owners to just focus on the mythical.  These types of animals require special care and we would want every animal to have the attention they need.</p>
            </dd>
            <dt>
                <a href="#accordion3" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion3" class="accordion-title accordionTitle js-accordionTrigger" style="font-size:17px">
                    Will you accept centaurs, mermaids, minotaurs, vampires, werewolves, or any animals kind of like theses?
                </a>
            </dt>
            <dd class="accordion-content accordionItem is-collapsed scrollable" id="accordion3" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size:15px">
                <p>No, for the most part, these aren't creatures that require our attention.  Most of these are considered to have human-like intelligence and can sustain themselves on their own.  If anyone has any of these creatures, just be warned that this could be seen as imprisonment or slavery and we recommend you releasing them safely.  We have come across the occasional incident where someone tries to drop off their little brother, grandma, or step-child.  We have to tell you that we do not accept ANY HUMANS! We can accept humanoids(beasts with human appearance or features but do not function as a human ie. Yeti, Sasquatch) but nothing that is or had an origin of human.</p>
            </dd>
        </dl>
    </div>
</div>

